    <item>
      <title>Understanding Equity and EV</title>
      <link>https://www.barge.org/understanding-equity-and-ev</link>
      <description>Many people don’t know the exact difference between equity and EV. In fact, some people use the terms as if they were identical.  Equity is the percentage chance that a hand will win after all the cards are dealt. The percentage chance includes splits and is utilized when comparing your holding against opponent’s hand(s) or range(s).</description>
